                id = "ownpoem", speaker = "Brother Faolan",
                text = "*(He stops vibrating. Goes very still.)* ...You weren't supposed to be able to see that. *(quietly, the acquisitive fever draining.)* Yes. Before the vows. I was going to write — something. A cycle of poems, about my mother, about the sea at Baldur's Gate, about — *(he falters.)* And then I took orders, and orders fill the hours, and the poems went *unwritten*, year on year, until they were just... an ache where a book should be. *(he looks at his ink-stained, scholarly hands.)* The Catalogue of the Unwritten lists *my* poems. The ones I'll never write now. I want to hold the book that proves they *almost existed* — proof that I was, for one young moment, a person with something to *say*, before I became a person who *files what others said.* *(his voice cracks.)* It's not for my career, Returned. It's so I can read the one page that's *mine* — the books I was, before I shelved myself. Bring it to me. Please. Let me see who I almost was.",
